President Trump addressed a gathering of law enforcement officials at the J.W. Marriott in Washington, D.C. He began by reading a section of the Immigration and Nationality Act that gives the President the power to restrict entry into the United States. He expressed frustration with the ongoing legal challenges to his travel ban executive order and criticized the courts for being political. He then shifted the focus to public safety and the need to support law enforcement. He highlighted the rise in violent crime in certain cities and emphasized the importance of working together to end the violence. He also pledged support for law enforcement and promised to increase resources and training. He called for a zero tolerance policy against violence towards law enforcement and expressed his commitment to building trust between law enforcement and the communities they serve. He also touched on the need to address the mental health crisis and the opioid epidemic. He concluded by expressing his gratitude and support for law enforcement and promising an open door policy at the White House.